functions.label: aggregateMappingAdditions
description:
Merge the added mappings from the given list of model changes.
Note: only changes of the `mappings_addition` type have mapping addition.

functions.label: assertValidModelVersion
description:
Asserts the provided number or string is a valid model version, and returns it.

A valid model version is a positive integer.

functions.label: buildModelVersionTransformFn
description: Build the transform function  for given model version, by chaining the transformations from its model changes.

functions.label: decodeRequestVersion
description:
Helper for decoding version to request params that are driven
by the version info
signature: (version: string | undefined) => { if_seq_no: number; if_primary_term: number; }

functions.label: decodeVersion
description:
Decode the "opaque" version string to the sequence params we
can use to activate optimistic concurrency in Elasticsearch

functions.label: encodeHitVersion
description:
Helper for encoding a version from a "hit" (hits.hits[#] from _search) or
"doc" (body from GET, update, etc) object

functions.label: encodeVersion
description:
Encode the sequence params into an "opaque" version string
that can be used in the saved object API in place of numeric
version numbers
signature: (seqNo: number | undefined, primaryTerm: number | undefined) => string

functions.label: getCurrentVirtualVersion
description:
Returns the current virtual version for the given type.
It will either be the latest model version if the type
already switched to using them (switchToModelVersionAt is set),
or the latest migration version for the type otherwise.

functions.label: getFieldListFromTypeMapping
description:
Return the list of fields present in the provided mappings.
Note that fields only containing properties are still considered fields by this function.

functions.label: getFieldListMapFromMappingDefinitions
description: Return the list of fields present in each individual type mappings present in the definition.

functions.label: getIndexForType
signature: ({ type, typeRegistry, defaultIndex, kibanaVersion, }: GetIndexForTypeOptions) => string

functions.label: getLatestModelVersion
description: Returns the latest registered model version number for the given type.

functions.label: getModelVersionDelta
description: Will generate the difference to go from `currentVersions` to `targetVersions`.

functions.label: getModelVersionMapForTypes
description: Build a version map for the given types.

functions.label: getRootProperties
description:
Get the property mappings for the root type in the EsMappingsDsl

 If the mappings don't have a root type, or the root type is not
 an object type (it's a keyword or something) this function will
 throw an error.

 EsPropertyMappings objects have the root property names as their
 first level keys which map to the mappings object for each property.
 If the property is of type object it too could have a `properties`
 key whose value follows the same format.

 This data can be found at `{indexName}.mappings.{typeName}.properties`
 in the es indices.get() response.

functions.label: getTypes
description: Get the names of the types defined in the EsMappingsDsl

functions.label: getVersionAddedFields
description: Return the list of fields, sorted, that were introduced in the given version.

functions.label: getVersionAddedMappings
description:
Return the mappings that were introduced in the given version.
If multiple 'mappings_addition' changes are present for the version,
they will be deep-merged.

functions.label: getVirtualVersionMap
description:
Returns a map of virtual model version for the given types.
See {@link getCurrentVirtualVersion}

functions.label: getVirtualVersionsFromMappingMeta
description: Build the version map from the specified source of the provided mappings meta.

functions.label: getVirtualVersionsFromMappings
description: Build the version map from the specified source of the provided mappings.

functions.label: isVirtualModelVersion
description:
Return true if the given semver version is a virtual model version.
Virtual model versions are version which major is the {@link modelVersionVirtualMajor}

functions.label: modelVersionToVirtualVersion
description: Returns the virtual version associated with the given model version

functions.label: virtualVersionToModelVersion
description: Converts a virtual model version to its model version.

children.label: appVersions
description: The latest model version of the types registered in the application

children.label: indexVersions
description: The model version stored in the index

children.label: deletedTypes
description: The list of deleted types to exclude during the compare process

misc.label: CompareModelVersionStatus
description:
The overall status of the model version comparison:
- `greater`: app version is greater than the index version
- `lesser`: app version is lesser than the index version
- `equal`: app version is equal to the index version
- `conflict`: app and index versions are incompatible (versions for some types are higher, and for other types lower)

misc.label: globalSwitchToModelVersionAt
description: The stack version where all types will be forced to switch to using the model version system.

misc.label: ModelVersionMap
description: A map of SO type name to Model Version.

misc.label: modelVersionVirtualMajor
description: The major version that is used to represent model versions.
